<subSubSection id="E67FC5059B84D1378F7B796071625560" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph id="EF73E4CAB94551E47EAFC81F6C651EC2" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0351971450A1B028FA0448186EA5CAED" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Overall brown. Pronotal disc of variable color, from having paired pink spots to entirely pink (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="116E8F8CC35190FD93A457E9DBB6249B" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6A, C, F</figureCitation>
), pronotal expansions dark brown, often brighter at anterior corners. Elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="290638835BF03EFB4205EE14DB2B5766" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6A, C</figureCitation>
) dark brown with a pale-yellow longitudinal stripe as long as about 4/5
<normalizedToken id="449752C465045C4AFEE8141BDFB3417A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
elytron length. Legs dark brown, except for trochanters, which are light brown. Sternum VIII with lateral vitreous spots. Pygidium brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="27DAAC4C49C89FDC59839B92CED2E17D" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="BDADF9FA2664B89C5F2FDD89BA64038E" doi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
<paragraph id="784B2314BF8791EFC8893A8ADB1E31FA" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
