<emphasis id="0E77BCEEA9F0F850E5E2629F0B387929" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">K</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="D04043F1610B567B41B20087126879A8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">L</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="C60A3295EA8A24228EC40115E0B25C30" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">M</emphasis>
, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="76C7B0BC4A32CD876EEC2E328E64E6F0" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F5801734C33D0E48F7ED79ECE8690911" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6F</figureCitation>
) with sides almost straight, mildly divergent posteriorly. 
<emphasis id="FE6773D906C90CF5A06778CD4EA2A03D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Male.</emphasis>
Total length = 8.4-8.8 mm (aver. 8.6 mm); Pronotal length = 1.8 mm; Pronotal width = 2.6-2.7 mm (aver. 2.65 mm); Elytral length = 6.0-6.6 mm (aver. 6.3 mm); Elytral width = 1.7-1.8 mm (aver. 1.75 mm). Antennomere III (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3C21585F708289A4A4F1E9D0279E800E" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6E</figureCitation>
) with lamella about 1.5
<normalizedToken id="5D0A3525EDCD8F22F3888D825950275A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than core antennomere. Sternum VI (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BBB4851E10E8415191EA59080C2CD20E" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6B, G</figureCitation>
) with a small lantern, occupying the medial 1/6 of sternum length, not reaching its anterior margin. Sternum VIII with posterior margin medially sinuose. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="23DB12771CB83B48D0FFCF19E9766C03" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6H</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, posterior corners barely visible, posterior margin medially mucronate. Syntergite (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5AD8B4A7F95470F45369CD0CBC92E992" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6I</figureCitation>
) boomerang-shaped (with anterior margin strongly curved). Phallus with dorsal plate bent dorsally (lateral view), with sides rounded at apical half, slightly convergent apically. Paramere (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E3E8972D862D23CAB462894036C02D83" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6K-M</figureCitation>
) apex curved ventrally, ventral projection (lateral view) well developed, almost right-angled. 
<emphasis id="63F31618738F402F795B7F578DCA6E3B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Female</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6B294CD16F605F8967E5EA74F830181F" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Costalampys bella sp. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antena, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Male terminal segments, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E; G); Scale bar: 0.5 mm (F; H-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543209" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">6C, D</figureCitation>
). Total length = 7.6 mm; Pronotal length = 1.5 mm; Pronotal width = 2.2 mm; Elytral length = 6.3 mm; Elytral width = 1.6 mm. Antennomeres III-X with apical corners almost right-angled, not projected, sterna VI and VII lacking lanterns.
